    <div class="nav-inner">
      <a href="#" class="nav-logo">
        <span class="nav-logo-mark">GO</span>
        <span class="nav-logo-name">Genevieve Ovsak</span>
      </a>
      <div class="nav-links" id="nav-links">
        <a href="#focus">Focus</a>
        <a href="#experience">Experience</a>
        <a href="#skills">Skills</a>
        <a href="#work">Work</a>
        <a href="#design">Design</a>
        <a href="#education">Education</a>
        <a href="#contact" class="nav-cta">Contact</a>
      </div>
      <button class="nav-mobile-btn" id="mobile-btn" aria-label="Toggle navigation">
        <span></span><span></span><span></span>
      </button>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- ── HERO ──────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="hero" class="hero">
    <div class="hero-bg"></div>
    <div class="hero-grid"></div>
    <div class="hero-orbs">
      <div class="orb orb-1"></div>
      <div class="orb orb-2"></div>
      <div class="orb orb-3"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="currently-badge">
        <span class="currently-dot"></span>
        Currently: Product Owner &amp; Lead Designer · Optum NPD
      </div>
      <h1 class="hero-name">
        Genevieve <span class="gradient-text">Ovsak</span>
      </h1>
      <div class="hero-callout">
        <span class="hero-callout-rule"></span>
        <span class="hero-callout-text">Product &times; Design &times; Engineering</span>
        <span class="hero-callout-rule"></span>
      </div>
      <p class="hero-tagline">
        I design systems that give people real visibility into their health — because information only helps if it's designed to be understood, not just seen.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a href="#work" class="btn btn-primary">See My Work</a>
        <a href="/resume.pdf" class="btn btn-secondary" download>↓ Resume</a>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-secondary">Get In Touch</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-stats">
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <span class="hero-stat-num">100K+</span>
          <span class="hero-stat-label">Target Users</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <span class="hero-stat-num">70+</span>
          <span class="hero-stat-label">Screens Designed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <span class="hero-stat-num">3</span>
          <span class="hero-stat-label">Platforms Built</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-stat">
          <span class="hero-stat-num">5TB</span>
          <span class="hero-stat-label">Data Secured</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="hero-location">
        <span class="hero-location-dot"></span>
        Maple Grove, MN
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── AREAS OF FOCUS ────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="focus" class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header fade-up">
        <span class="section-label">Areas of Focus</span>
          <h2>What I Do</h2>
        <p class="section-desc">
          A deliberately multi-disciplinary background built to operate across domains,
          each discipline informing and sharpening the others.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="focus-grid fade-up">
        <div class="focus-card">
          <p class="focus-num">01</p>
          <h3>AI Product Strategy</h3>
          <p>Roadmaps, requirements, and safety guardrails for AI-integrated products in regulated environments, including direct experience defining what AI should and shouldn't do when patient outcomes are downstream.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="focus-card">
          <p class="focus-num">02</p>
          <h3>UX &amp; Product Design</h3>
          <p>Research-driven, accessible design for complex multi-role systems. WCAG 2.1 AAA applied as a foundational constraint, shaping decisions around font scaling, screen reader behavior, and high-contrast across every surface.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="focus-card">
          <p class="focus-num">03</p>
          <h3>Biomedical Sciences</h3>
          <p>B.S. Biology &amp; IT, with genuine domain fluency in aging-in-place monitoring, remote sensing, and clinical-adjacent workflows, built through hands-on research and direct healthcare product work.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="focus-card">
          <p class="focus-num">04</p>
          <h3>Data &amp; Analytics</h3>
          <p>Hands-on data analysis using R, SQL, and Tableau, focused on translating raw data into decisions rather than just dashboards. Includes biostatistics coursework and experience presenting quantitative analysis to senior leadership.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="focus-card">
          <p class="focus-num">05</p>
          <h3>Software Engineering</h3>
          <p>Full-stack enough to write the API contract, review a PR, and define error states alongside engineers, bridging product intent and technical execution without losing fidelity in translation.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── EXPERIENCE ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section id="experience" class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header fade-up">
        <span class="section-label">The Work</span>
        <h2>Experience</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline">

        <div class="timeline-item fade-up">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-card">
            <div class="timeline-meta">
              <span class="timeline-period">2025 — Present</span>
              <span class="timeline-location">Eden Prairie, MN</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="timeline-role">Product Owner &amp; Lead Product Designer</h3>
            <p class="timeline-company">Optum Enterprise Solutions · UnitedHealth Group · New Product Development</p>
            <ul class="timeline-bullets">
              <li>Own product vision, roadmap, requirements, and pilot strategy for Violet, a consumer-first caregiver support and aging-in-place platform; authored 100+ user stories spanning onboarding, provisioning, notifications, accessibility, data visualization, and security. The non-clinical consumer framing shaped every downstream architecture and UX decision.</li>
              <li>Sole designer of 70+ screens across 3 platforms: led a full phased UI migration from Flutter prototype to production React Native, built a 27-component design system and 14-category web component library, and enforced WCAG 2.1 AAA throughout, covering font scaling, screen reader support, and high-contrast modes across every surface.</li>
              <li>Designed, built, and own an internal developer admin portal in Next.js + React: analytics views across user engagement, device health, and anomaly detection; caregiver management with health variable trending; activity log ingestion from Splunk; and 4-breakpoint responsiveness. 151 TypeScript files shipped.</li>
              <li>Led architecture sessions defining the platform's identity and access model: UUID-based user identity, enterprise SSO, a platform-owned proxy API, RBAC, and many-to-many caregiver–patient relationships.</li>
              <li>Specified product behavior for sensing and alerts: a sensor-driven risk score projecting likelihood of health change over a rolling window, a tiered notification system with emergency, daily, and weekly delivery modes including suppression and quiet hours, third-party device integration via event streaming, and AI chatbot guardrails scoped to informational responses with mandatory human escalation.</li>
              <li>Defined API contracts and error states to keep backend teams unblocked; coordinated identity provider setup, OAuth/PKCE mobile auth, wireless IoT device pairing, and PHI compliance toward ~100K users; remediated security vulnerabilities across multiple audit cycles; ran 5 discovery cycles including a demo to 35 senior leaders, designed two onboarding flows, and established pilot readiness criteria and a product scorecard.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="tags">
              <span class="tag">Product Strategy</span>
              <span class="tag">AI Integration</span>
              <span class="tag">UX Design</span>
              <span class="tag">Flutter / React Native</span>
              <span class="tag">Design Systems</span>
              <span class="tag">WCAG AAA</span>
              <span class="tag">Healthcare</span>
              <span class="tag">PHI / Privacy</span>
              <span class="tag">Azure B2C</span>
              <span class="tag">Kafka</span>
              <span class="tag">Systems Architecture</span>
              <span class="tag">IoT / Device Provisioning</span>
              <span class="tag">Agile / Scrum</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item fade-up">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-card">
            <div class="timeline-meta">
              <span class="timeline-period">Summer 2024</span>
              <span class="timeline-location">Eden Prairie, MN</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="timeline-role">Full Stack Developer & Scrum Master</h3>
            <p class="timeline-company">UnitedHealth Group — Technology Development Program (TDP)</p>
            <ul class="timeline-bullets">
              <li>Built an internal cybersecurity workflow tool using Python, Vue, and FastAPI to consolidate domain-blocking workflows that previously required manual coordination across multiple systems into a single analyst interface.</li>
              <li>Served as Scrum Master, facilitating agile ceremonies and aligning cross-functional delivery across the internship team.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="tags">
              <span class="tag">Python</span>
              <span class="tag">Vue</span>
              <span class="tag">FastAPI</span>
              <span class="tag">Scrum Master</span>
              <span class="tag">Cybersecurity</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item fade-up">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-card">
            <div class="timeline-meta">
              <span class="timeline-period">Summer 2023</span>
              <span class="timeline-location">Eden Prairie, MN</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="timeline-role">Software Developer Intern</h3>
            <p class="timeline-company">Optum Technology · UnitedHealth Group</p>
            <ul class="timeline-bullets">
              <li>Engineered an encryption pipeline for ~5TB of sensitive, searchable data, improving integrity, protection, and retrieval performance across a regulated data environment.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="tags">
              <span class="tag">Python</span>
              <span class="tag">Data Engineering</span>
              <span class="tag">Security</span>
              <span class="tag">Regulated Environments</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item fade-up">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-card">
            <div class="timeline-meta">
              <span class="timeline-period">Summer 2022</span>
              <span class="timeline-location">Greenville, SC</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="timeline-role">Bioinformatics Research Fellow</h3>
            <p class="timeline-company">Furman University</p>
            <ul class="timeline-bullets">
              <li>Improved a Dual-RNA-Seq visualization tool by adding new chart types and view modes; validated changes through structured user studies following a research → prototype → iterate methodology.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="tags">
              <span class="tag">Bioinformatics</span>
              <span class="tag">Data Visualization</span>
              <span class="tag">User Research</span>
              <span class="tag">Prototyping</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-item fade-up">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-card">
            <div class="timeline-meta">
              <span class="timeline-period">2022 — 2025</span>
              <span class="timeline-location">SC / NC / Remote</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="timeline-role">Motion Graphics & Camera Professional</h3>
            <p class="timeline-company">ESPN+ · CBS/ESPNU · Bon Secours Wellness Arena · Freelance</p>
            <ul class="timeline-bullets">
              <li>Produced broadcast-quality motion graphics and live camera work for D1 athletics on ESPN+ and CBS/ESPNU: basketball, football, soccer, volleyball, softball, and lacrosse; operated PTZ and handheld cameras for arena events, deployed graphics via Ross Systems/Xpression, and supported remote productions through Tupelo Honey Production.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="tags">
              <span class="tag">Broadcast Production</span>
              <span class="tag">Motion Graphics</span>
              <span class="tag">Ross Systems</span>
              <span class="tag">ESPN+ / CBS</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
